author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump was hit by a bathroom door aboard Air Force One as someone tried to leave the restroom while he was talking to reporters. It happened as the president flew to Pennsylvania to tout his economic agenda, but it turned into an R-rated spectacle. He took special aim at Democratic Representative Ilhan Omar, who was born in Somalia and is a US citizen. Omar condemned the remarks as "bigoted lies" and called the president "a national embarrassment."
title: President Trump's Visit To Pennsylvania Turns Into R-Rated Spectacle

author: Inside Edition
description: After eating the food they Doordashed to their Indiana home, Marc Cardin says his wife started coughing before throwing up. When Cardin watched the footage from the doorbell camera, he noticed the driver spraying something that he believed was pepper spray right on the bag. In a statement, Doordash says, "We have zero tolerance for this type of appalling behavior," and the driver has been permanently removed from the platform. They also say they are cooperating with the investigation.
title: Did This Doordash Driver Spray Pepper Spray On Food Order?

author: Inside Edition
description: All of the employees at a Hardee's fast food restaurant vanished. Customers at the Hardee's in Missouri called 911. Ryan Eggers, a customer who called 911, spoke with Inside Edition. Police arrived at the scene. They found condiments and cheese left out in the open and food still cooking but no employees. According to a social media post, there was a dispute among employees and they all left mid-shift. Inside Edition reached out to Hardee's corporate office for comment but did not hear back.
title: Customers Go To A Hardee's Restaurant And Find No Employees

author: Inside Edition
description: Remarkable video captured the moment a plane emergency landed on a Florida highway. A woman was at the wheel when the twin-engined plane landed on top of her car. The 57-year-old driver sustained only minor injuries. James Coffey and his son Peter captured the crash video. A nurse who was on the scene climbed over the highway divider to help. Inside Edition spoke to nurse Annie Wigley and her husband Bernard. Police say the pilot and his passenger were both unhurt.
title: Video Captures Moment Plane Lands On Car On Florida Highway

author: Inside Edition
description: Armed police officers pulled up to a house searching for a wanted fugitive. They fired bean bags at a vehicle before the suspect emerged. In a shocking twist, authorities opened a shed on the property and small children exited the shed. One of the children told officers there was an infant inside in a crib. Body camera footage showed the squalid conditions in the shed. In all, there were five children in the shed where authorities say they believe the children were living.
title: Cops Find 5 Children Locked In Shed While Searching For Fugitive

author: Inside Edition
description: "CBS Mornings'" co-host Tony Dokoupil has been named the new anchor of "CBS Evening News." Gayle King made the big announcement. "CBS Evening News" has been on the air since 1948, most famously anchored by the legendary Walter Cronkite. Dokoupil, 44, will replace the current anchors, Maurice DuBois and John Dickerson. Dokoupil will begin going up against David Muir at ABC and Tom Llamas at NBC.
title: Tony Dokoupil Named New Anchor Of 'CBS Evening News'

author: Inside Edition
description: Dramatic bodycam footage shows cops with the Sanford Police Department in Florida running into a burning home in early December to save the people inside, and then going back in to rescue the family dog. The husky was found unconscious and was rushed out of the home and given oxygen and CPR before regaining conscious.
title: Police Give Dog CPR After Burning Home Rescue

description: Chilling video played at the trial of Brian Walshe, who is accused of killing and dismembering his wife. Prosecutors say it shows Walshe shopping at a Lowe's home improvement store.
title: Security Video Shows Brian Walshe Day After His Wife Disappeared #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: In her best news anchor voice, Carissa Codel read some of the meanest comments.
title: TV News Anchor Reads Trolls' Comments About Her Weight #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Chilling video played at the trial of Brian Walshe, who is accused of killing and dismembering his wife. Prosecutors say it shows Walshe shopping at a Lowe's home improvement store. The video was dated January 1, 2023, the day after Walshe's wife, Ana was last seen alive. The receipt shows he bought a hacksaw, a utility knife, tin snips, a hammer, latex gloves, a mop and buckets. Walshe pled guilty to improperly disposing of his wife's body, but he maintains he did not kill her.
title: Security Video Shows Brian Walshe Day After His Wife Was Last Seen

author: Inside Edition
description: A woman was trapped in her car after officials in Wisconsin say she was hit on a highway and went up onto the retaining wall. The Milwaukee County Sheriff's Office says the best way to get her out was to break the car's back window and have her crawl out. Fire officials were on hand to help assist her as she made her way out of the vehicle. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Driver Rescued From Car Hanging Over Retaining Wall After Accident

author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition spoke exclusively to father-of-two Logan Gregoire, who suffered no major injuries.
title: Iowa Dad Survives Train Crashing Into His Car #shorts
